Cell.Text: Have you decided to do the right thing, Dragonborn?
I wish there were another way, Dragonborn, but it falls to you to serve justice upon Paarthurnax.
Make your choice, Dragonborn. You're either with us or against us.
Justice can be harsh. But it is still justice. Paarthurnax deserves to die.
[S] I knew we could count on you! Glad to have you back on our side.
[S] At long last. An ancient evil is avenged. The shades of many Blades salute you this day.

Here's the big picture. He helped Alduin enslave our ancestors. He may have betrayed Alduin in the end, but that makes him worse, not better. | We can't afford to give Paarthurnax the opportunity to betray us in turn, and return to his old master.

Paarthurnax was the author of many atrocities during the Dragon War - crimes great enough to be remembered for thousands of years. | True, he turned traitor to Alduin and helped overthrow the Dragon Cult, but that does not excuse or expiate his previous deeds. | Whether or not he has truly repented, or merely acted to save himself, justice demands that he pay with his life.

Node.Caption: MQPaarthurnaxA2: Why does he need to die?

Cell.Text: Dragons were made to dominate. The will to power is in our blood. | I can be trusted. I know this. But I don't expect anyone else to believe it. It is always wise to mistrust a dragon. | I have overcome my nature only through great effort and long study of the Way of the Voice. | Not a day goes by where I am not tempted to return to my inborn nature. | What is better - to overcome your evil nature through great effort, or to be born good?
The Blades are wise not to trust me. I wouldn't trust another dragon.

Node.Caption: MQ204PaarBladesTopic: The Blades say you deserve to die.

Cell.Text: [S] S|Now you see why I've warned you against them! Bloodthirsty barbarians!

Node.Caption: MQPaarthurnaxGreybeardsTopic: The Blades want me to kill Paarthurnax.

Cell.Text: Yes. But understand - during the days of Alduin's rule, all dragons were his allies. There was nothing else they could be. | If not for Paarthurnax, Alduin could not have been overthrown. It was he that first taught men to use the thu'um.

Node.Caption: MQPaarthurnaxGreybeardsA1: Is it true what they said? Was he Alduin's ally?

Cell.Text: The same could be said for any of us, could it not? Are you so guiltless as to stand in judgment upon Paarthurnax? | Listen to your inner Voice before acting. Do not allow the Blades to bully you into doing something you will later regret. | After all, repentance is something you deny to Paarthurnax by meting out your so-called justice.

Node.Caption: MQPaarthurnaxGreybeardsB1: He still needs to pay for his crimes.

Cell.Text: You're learning, Dragonborn. Doing nothing can be the wisest choice, although strangely often the most difficult. | I trust that you will make the right choice, in the end. Listen to the Voice that Kynareth has placed within you, and your path will be clear.

Node.Caption: MQPaarthurnaxGreybeardsB2: I haven't decided what to do yet.

Cell.Text: Kynareth has placed the Voice of wisdom within you, Dragonborn. All you need do is learn to listen to it, and your path will be clear.

Node.Caption: MQPaarthurnaxGreybeardsB3: Don't worry, I'm not going to kill Paarthurnax.

Cell.Text: [S] G|This is how you repay our trust? Paarthurnax's trust? | His noble spirit... the wisdom of ages... his deep understanding of our existence... all gone, and for what? | A mindless vendetta urged on you by a cabal of Akaviri barbarians! | Begone, before even my philosophy is tested beyond the breaking point. We are men of peace, and you are not.
G|<<Shared>> We have nothing to say to each other. Paarthurnax's murder is beyond my powers of forgiveness.

Cell.Text: There's one more thing. We know about Paarthurnax.
I'm afraid there's a further problem. A serious one. I've discovered who the Greybeards' leader really is.

Node.Caption: MQPaarthurnaxIntroTopic: What about Paarthurnax?

Cell.Text: Paarthurnax. The dragon, that the Greybeards have been protecting for all these years.
You've discovered... what?
He's a dragon. Not just any dragon, but the right hand of Alduin, responsible for many atrocities during the ancient Dragon War.

Node.Caption: MQPaarthurnaxIntroA1: You know... what?

Cell.Text: [S] He needs to die. He deserves to die. And it falls to you to kill him. | Until he's dead... well, I'm sorry, but we would dishonor our oaths as Blades if we continued to help you.

[S] The Blades have been hunting him for centuries, but he was protected by the Greybeards and then the Emperors. | Justice demands that he die for his crimes. Until he is dead, I'm afraid my oath as a Blade prevents me from offering you aid and comfort.

Node.Caption: MQPaarthurnaxIntroB1

Cell.Text: That's fine. We needed his help. Now we don't, and it's long past time for him to pay for his crimes. | And he's not just any dragon. He was the right hand of Alduin. | He committed atrocities so infamous they are still remembered, thousands of years later.

All well and good. But did you know that he was Alduin's chief lieutenant in ancient times? Responsible for terrible atrocities? | It's true that his crimes are long in the past, but justice does not count the passage of years.

Node.Caption: MQPaarthurnaxIntroA2: Turns out he's a dragon. But he helped me.
